Nigeria to Prosecute Troops Over Maiduguri Killings, Nation Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-07-28T08:30:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/nigeria-to-prosecute-troops-over-maiduguri-killings-nation-says.html
Five Nigerian soldiers will face
trial for violating the rules of engagement by retaliating for a
bomb attack targeting troops in Maiduguri on July 23, the Nation
newspaper reported, citing the chief of defense staff, Air
Marshal Oluseyi Petinrin.  At least 20 people were killed by troops after the blast
that injured three soldiers, the Lagos-based newspaper said
today, citing a report by  Amnesty International .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 